articles.title: Justin Bieber sells music catalogue for $USD200M - Sky News Australia
articles.description:
Justin Bieber has sold his music rights to Blackstone-backed Hipgnosis Songs Capital for a reported $USD200 million.

The singer sold the rights to every song he’s released up until December 2021 to Hipgnosis Songs Capital.
